<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>My Website</title>
  <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>
  <script>
    $(document).ready(function() {
      // Add a click event listener to the button
      $('button').on('click', function() {
        // Code to execute when the button is clicked
        console.log("Button clicked!");
      });
    });
  </script>
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Your HTML code here -->
</body>
</html>
This code adds a click event listener to the <button> element using jQuery's .on() method, and logs a message to the console when the button is clicked. You can replace the console.log statement with your desired functionality, such as displaying a modal or navigating to another page.





